                <h3>Brand Old (School)</h3>
                <p>I began letting the research that we'd done make its way into something new. I started with a single image, like a poster, print ad or sticker, thinking about a personality. All the audio hardware people we talked to loved had quirks, odd shapes, unique feels. It all had weight and edges and texture and made a unique impression. Each instrument was a character, and I was building a world for it to live in.</p>
                <p>I went through several design concepts before settling on something that spoke to our target audiences, had an aesthetic I could build on, and most importantly, felt like the start of a world that you wanted to inhabit.</p>
