                <h3>Menus Level Deep</h3>
                <p>AnalogKit was ultimately about building instruments, and synths are deeply complicated, so I worked with our devs on an extensible system control panels which, like real synths, were intuitive and powerful  but also made you feel really cool to use.</p>
                <p>As the app got more complex and acquired more (and more) modules, I usertested several types of menu for accessing and organizing components, before settling on a system for helper text, module documentation and  quick and advanced module controls.</p>
                <p>In testing, users were able to to play and enjoy the example projects, but struggled with  building and modifying projects. I  wrote and designed a tutorial system based on their feedback that  helped them get started.</p>
            </div>
