                <h3>Bittersweet Polyphony</h3>
                <p>AnalogKit got a great reception in the synth and DIY music communities. We did a Reddit AMA, several podcasts and had great reviews on popular YouTube channels.  It didn’t hit with a wide audience like Cleartune, but I learned a lot about building component libraries  and the journey from design spec to finished product.</p>
<p>Swap meet, AnalogKit’s sharing marketplace, continues to host some great user-generated projects, including visualizers, games and of course lots of audio toys.</p>
<p>My learnings from AnalogKit informed a lot of the training that I’ve done since, and even though we didn’t get rich, it was a great experience.</p>
